div.div:
Data from XNAT is extracted and loaded to the SQLite database.
The raw data is transformed according to the NIDM and FHIR v4 specifications.
The delta is calculated at this stage to improve load performance in SQLite and Blue Brain Nexus.
The scripts that perform this step are in nexus_etl/src_to_dw folder.

div.div:
Once the data is in SQLIte, it can then be loaded to Blue Brain Nexus.
For performance reasons, only the new/updated data is loaded to Nexus during each run instead of a full refresh.
Scripts for this step can be found in dw_to_nexus folder.
